 erinnert er sich an Derrida und fragt, was es heißt, einen Philosophen als Lehrer zu haben.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aDekonstruktion. 4aFranzösische Philosophiegeschichte. 4aPhilosophie. 4aPhilosophiegeschichte. 4aPoststrukturalismus. 4aSozialität. 4aSprache. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh  aFrench History of Philosophy.  aHistory of Philosophy.  aLanguage.  aPhilosophy.  aPost-structuralism.  aSocial Relations.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highlight Collection Complete Package 2000-2009z9783110463415oZDB-23-TSO08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highlight Collection Geschichte 2000-2009z978311046334740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839407400zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839407400423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839407400/original  a978-3-11-046334-7  transcript Highlight Collection Geschichte 2000-2009c2000d2009  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-TSOc2000d2009